ption (third conjecture)\nthat $f_{k,n}(x)\\neq0$ for $k=(l,\\dots,1)$, $n=(l-1,\\dots,0)$ and every $x>0$.\nOur more general result implies all the above conjectures, together with their\ncorollary for the overdamped model of the Josephson junction in\nsuperconductivity: the description of adjacency points of phase-lock areas as\nsolutions of explicit analytic equations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 5 Sep 2015 18:15:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 Oct 2015 08:45:11 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 18 May 2016 18:53:36 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 1 Nov 2016 17:52:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-21"}
